      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just \"mimicking\" though. the stuff being posted is so specific to things only i would know. it's like it's living my life for me while i'm just sitting here. if an AI can do that, how can i even prove it's not me? it feels like my actual identity has been hijacked and replaced by this digital version of me that's doing things i'd never do. is there any way to tell if an account is being run by a bot that's been trained on your soul or whatever?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
